<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
	Privacy manifest for the NALI Migraine Log watchOS bundle.

	IMPORTANT: keep this comment block OUTSIDE the <plist> root element.
	App Store Connect's server-side validator (the one that emits
	ITMS-91056) is a separate code path from `plutil`. We have observed
	that it mis-flags manifests with comments interleaved between
	<key>/<value>/<dict>/<array> nodes inside the plist data, even though
	such comments are valid XML and `plutil -lint` accepts them. Apple's
	own published manifest examples (TN3183) contain zero comments inside
	the plist body. To stay safely compatible with both validators we put
	all human-readable rationale here in the XML prolog, where it cannot
	be confused for plist content.

	Sibling files that MUST stay in lockstep:
	  - NALI Migraine Log/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy            (iOS)
	  - NALI Migraine Log macOS/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy
	  - NALI Migraine Log Watch App Watch App/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy   (this file)
	Apple does not allow under-declaration; over-declaration is harmless.

	Top-level keys, and why each is or is not present
	-------------------------------------------------
	NSPrivacyTracking            present, set to false. We do not link
	                             any data collected by this app with
	                             data collected by other companies'
	                             apps, websites, or properties.

	NSPrivacyTrackingDomains     OMITTED. Per TN3181, when
	                             NSPrivacyTracking is false this key
	                             must be omitted entirely; an empty
	                             array there is the documented trigger
	                             for ITMS-91056.

	NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes  OMITTED. Apple's TN3181 does not list
	                             this key in any of its tables, and the
	                             TN3183 example template does not
	                             include it. We do not collect data and
	                             send it to a server we control. iCloud
	                             sync uses the user's own private
	                             CloudKit database; new entries are
	                             also relayed to the paired iPhone via
	                             WatchConnectivity, but that is a peer-
	                             to-peer hand-off, not developer-side
	                             data collection. An earlier revision
	                             of this file shipped the key as
	                             <array/> because Xcode's "Generate
	                             Privacy Report" tool emits "Missing an
	                             expected key:
	                             'NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes'" when
	                             it's absent — that warning is purely
	                             informational and does NOT block
	                             uploads. App Store Connect's validator,
	                             which DOES block uploads, has been
	                             observed to reject the empty array,
	                             so the key is omitted here. If we ever
	                             start collecting data, add the key
	                             back with one or more populated
	                             dictionaries — never as an empty array.

	NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes    Required-reason API declarations,
	                             using Apple's published reason codes
	                             from TN3183. Each dictionary inside
	                             the array contains exactly the two
	                             required keys.

	Required-reason API entries declared below
	------------------------------------------
	NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults / CA92.1
	    Used by the MigrationCoordinator to record the last-launched
	    app version on the watch and by shared services that read
	    settings written by the iOS app. All values are read and
	    written exclusively by this app.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>
	<false/>
	<key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
	<array>
		<dict>
			<key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>
			<string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults</string>
			<key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>
			<array>
				<string>CA92.1</string>
			</array>
		</dict>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
